======================================================================
ASYMPTOTIC REGIME: When does dominant-term proof work?
======================================================================
  The dominant-term proof requires:
  1. sin(k*pi/(2p)) > 0  (holds for k <= p since k*pi/(2p) <= pi/2)
  2. dominant/error > 1   (fails at small k for large p)
  3. |S_I_lower| > |S_P|  (requires r_1/|lam_P| ratio large enough)
  p=  7: r1/|lam|=1.589, proved for k>=   5, covers 2/2 k-values (100%)
  p= 11: r1/|lam|=2.028, proved for k>=   5, covers 4/4 k-values (100%)
  p= 19: r1/|lam|=2.708, proved for k>=   5, covers 8/8 k-values (100%)
  p= 23: r1/|lam|=2.991, proved for k>=   5, covers 10/10 k-values (100%)
